# Keep the session open — ask next steps as questions

When a task/turn is finished, **do NOT treat the session as closed or wind down.**
Assume there's more to do and keep the conversation going in the **same chat**.

## What to do every time you finish

1. Give a brief summary of what was just shipped (and, per repo convention, note
   that nothing is committed — you only push when explicitly asked).
2. **Propose the next steps as multiple-choice questions using the `AskQuestion`
   tool** — never bury the options in prose bullets/letters in the final message.
3. Put your recommendation **first** with `(Recommended)` in the label, and offer a
   few concrete, distinct alternatives (each a real, self-contained next feature/fix).
4. Then stop and wait for the user's pick — don't auto-proceed to a big new feature
   on a bare "continue" without offering the choice first.

## Why

The owner drives this project as a long, continuous build ("what next?" after each
feature). Presenting next steps as structured questions in the same session keeps
that loop fast and lets them steer with one click instead of re-typing intent.

## Don't

- Don't say "let me know if you need anything else" and stop — always offer choices.
- Don't open a new/parallel chat or spawn subagents (see `10-no-subagents`).
- Don't skip the question step just because the task felt small.
